‘As part of our next Android release, encryption will be enabled by default out of the box, so you won't even have to think about turning it on, ’ said Google’s director of global communications and public affairs Niki Christoff.

‘For over three years Android has offered encryption, and keys are not stored off of the device, so they cannot be shared with law enforcement.’

