The reference to competitors is believed to have been an attack on Google, which the firm has countered with its Android L encryption announcement today.

The rollout of new software to Google devices, however, is significantly slower than Apple.

Apple can push updates to every device because it owns the hardware, but Android runs on the devices of multiple manufacturers, which will have to roll out Android L individually.

This could take months, if not years.  

